<p>I'm trying to transform this string</p>  <pre><code>.jpg,.gif,.png </code></pre>  <p>into this (not dots and space after comma)</p>  <pre><code>jpg, gif, png </code></pre>  <p>I thought that something like <a href="http://php.net/manual/en/function.str-replace.php" rel="nofollow">PHP's <code>str_replace</code></a> for arrays in JS will do the trick, so I found <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/5069464/replace-multiple-strings-at-once">this post</a>, and specifically <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/a/5069776/702353">this answer</a>. I tried it but is't not working as expected. I'm getting a blank string... Am I doing something wrong?</p>  <p>JS</p>  <pre><code>String.prototype.replaceArray = function(find, replace) {     var replaceString = this;     var regex;      for (var i = 0; i &lt; find.length; i++)     {         regex = new RegExp(find[i], "g");         replaceString = replaceString.replace(regex, replace[i]);     }      return replaceString; };  var my_string = ".jpg,.gif,.png";  alert(my_string.replaceArray([".", ","],["", ", "])); </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://jsfiddle.net/4uwgytos/" rel="nofollow">Link to jsfiddle</a></p>